README for xfce4-session 4.2.x

REQUIREMENTS

PRE-INSTALL

POST-INSTALL

To enable the restart/shutdown functionality of the xfce4 session 
manager you have to install sudo:

  1. install /usr/ports/contrib/sudo
  2. edit /etc/sudoers with visudo as root and add a line like:
  
     %users ALL = NOPASSWD: /usr/lib/xfce4/xfsm-shutdown-helper

PRECAUTION


